In England, in the seven days to 15 December, there were 416,458 new confirmed cases (736.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 December, there were 289,721 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 44% (126,737 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 20 December is 9,731,126 (17,208 cases per 100,000 population).
